	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)">Office of <persName>ALLEN &#38; CO.</persName>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>4 BROAD STREET</placeName>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; <date>Dec 18 1865</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. I Leeser</addressee>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir and friend&#44;</p>
				<p>I am sorry that I have not been<lb/> able to see you lately&#44; but my visits<lb/> to <hi rend="underline">home</hi> have been so irregular and<lb/> uncertain that I have not been able to<lb/> call to see you.  The man&#44; I<lb/> forget his name who keep Hebrew<lb/> Book Store on <placeName>East Broadway</placeName>&#44; <hi rend="underline"><persName>Laight</persName></hi><lb/> I think is his name&#44; <del>called</del> he is<lb/> &#8220;Shamas&#8221; of <placeName>Henry St</placeName> Synagogue&#44; wants his<lb/> Bill from you&#44; please send it to me.<lb/>  Have you any of <persName>Mr <hi rend="underline">De Sola&#39;s</hi></persName> <hi rend="underline">catechisms</hi><lb/> if so please send 25 with Bill for<lb/> Hebrew Free School.  Did you receive a small<lb/> check of about &#36;14&#61; I sent you last week<lb/> We are all well&#44; Very truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">M. M. Allen</persName>.</p>
		</body>
